            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_33gc' title='Col. 33GC &mdash; HL Deb 07 July 2003 vol 651 c33GC' name='column_33gc' href='#column_33gc' rel='bookmark'>33GC</a>
            an order made in a state of emergency as distinct from orders made otherwise. On those there is a serious argument about arbitration hut, on the emergency aspect, there is not. Action may have to be taken at any time, but what would happen?</p><p>
